    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-06-08T14:58:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-06-08T14:58:00-05:00" n="220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <head>220. Message From President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1" type="from"
                        >Johnson</persName> to Premier <persName corresp="#p_KAN1" type="to"
                        >Kosygin</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d220fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_JLB1"
                            >Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File, Head of State
                        Correspondence, <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>, Washington-Moscow
                        “Hot-Line” Exchange, 6/5–10/67. No classification marking. A typed notation
                        on the message indicates it was approved by the President at 3:36 p.m.;
                        transmitted by U.S. <gloss target="#t_MOLINK1">Molink</gloss> at 3:58 p.m.;
                        and received by Soviet <gloss target="#t_MOLINK1">Molink</gloss> at 4
                        p.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-06-08T15:58:00-04:00">June 8, 1967, 3:58 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KAN1">Kosygin</persName>,</p>
                <p>I deeply appreciate your transmitting the message to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_NGA1">Nasser</persName>. We lost 10 men, 16 critically wounded,
                    and 65 wounded, as a result of Israeli attack, for which they have
                    apologized.</p>
                <p>Respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Lyndon B. Johnson</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
